title: For Sale:  "No Gunsmith" Mosin Nagant Scope Mount
postcontent:
NEW Model Mosin Nagant Scout Scope Mount with high tensile strength alloy steel mounting bolt and nut. $22.95 + $5.95  Shipping & Insurance. We accept USPS money orders and PayPal.

This is the newest model in the family of “No-Gunsmith” Mosin Nagant scout scope mounts. It replaces the rear sight and features a high tensile cross bolt and nut that fits completely through the mount to lock it into place. No more stripped threads or broken screws. 

Restore your rifle to its original configuration by unbolting the mount and reinstalling the rear sight. Fits most models, including the Russian M91/30 & M91/38 rifles, Finnish M27, M28 and M91/30 rifles and all versions of the M-38, M-44, M53 and M56 carbines. Use with Weaver style rings (not included) to mount Hologram, Red Dot and extended eye relief (EER) scopes. 

Earlier model mounts were designed with two short bolts that threaded into the sides of the mount through the rear sight base ears. With extended shooting these bolts could strip out the threads in the mount and it would become loose. This new Scope Mount has been threaded completely through and fitted with a full length threaded cross bolt and locking nut that securely attaches the scope mount to the rear sight base. 

Installation instructions included. Send your email address for ordering information.

title: For Sale:  Mauser 98K Scout Scope Mount
postcontent:
During WWII, German field commanders requested some rifles be equipped with telescopic sights for issue to combat troops.  These were not sniper rifles, but standard combat model rifles for use in the field. The solution was to modify the rifle to accept a "scout scope" with an extended eye relief and mounted forward of the action.

Surplus Mauser military rifles are readily available today and many shooters have opted to use telescopic sights on these rifles. Until recently, this involved drilling and tapping the receiver, bending the bolt and modifying the stock - an expensive modification to a collectible rifle. 

This easy installation, "no gunsmithing" mount replaces the rear sight leaf. Simply remove the rear sight leaf and spring, insert and bolt in the mount. Attach Weaver style rings (not included) to the Picatinny mount and install your favorite Hologram, Red Dot or extended eye relief (EER) scope. Restore the rifle to its original configuration by unbolting the mount and reinstalling the rear sight.

Send email address for ordering information.

USPS shipping & insurance - $5.95.   We accept PAYPAL and US Postal Money Orders.
